               <provenance>According to Additio 1, Gabra Ṣādǝq donated
                     the Ms. to the church of Dändära Mikāʾel. His name and the name of his wife,
                     ʾAmata Mikāʾel, were written in supplication formulas over the (sometimes
                     erased) names of the original donors, probably in the same hand that wrote
                     Additio 1. The names of the original donors can be deciphered as Walda Mikāʾel
                     and Walatta Gärima (s. 19ra, 28vb, 32va); the
                     name of Tasfā ʾIyasus is written on 57ra.</provenance></history>
